# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug
target

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/
screenshot.png
screenshot.request
fx*.png
# Ctrl+P debug region captures (see src/region_capture.rs). Ephemeral; the folder's CLAUDE.md is kept.
debug_screenshots/*.png

# Offline behaviour-search outputs (see src/squad_ai/coevolve.rs). Regenerated by `train prior` /
# `train evolve`; nothing in the shipped game reads them. The prior is a frozen reference the search
# reproduces from the authored brains, and the elite archives churn every run — committing either would
# version stale, machine-generated data. A *blessed* archive, once one is adopted into the game, gets a
# distinct committed name.
assets/config/baseline_prior.ron
# Every `elites_*.ron` is a machine-generated search output (squad/swarm/world/levels/audio/behavior/policy
# co-evolution + neuroevolution + POET). None are read by the shipped game; a *blessed* archive adopted into
# the game gets a distinct committed name.
assets/config/elites_*.ron

# `cargo train` island-model output: per-island archives + logs from a parallel search fan-out. Same
# rationale as elites_*.ron — machine-generated; the winner is applied via `train apply`, never committed here.
islands_out/

# Snapshots of every archive that was ever baked (`train apply` keeps one per bake so an old elite stays
# reviewable after the next run overwrites `elites_*.ron`). Machine-generated and potentially large, same as
# the archives they copy — but note the *ledger* that indexes them, BAKES.md, IS tracked: it is the review
# trail for a moved golden, and a review trail nobody else can see is not one.
assets/config/bake_history/

# Claude Code per-project state (worktrees from other sessions, settings, transcripts) — never commit
.claude/

# Per-developer Cargo overrides (e.g. a machine-specific build.target-dir for local build isolation).
# MUST NOT be committed: a hardcoded absolute path broke CI on ubuntu-latest for every commit
# ("failed to create directory /Users/…: Permission denied"). Each machine keeps its own local copy.
.cargo/config.toml
